I'm curious about the exhibition Transitions 2 by @baars_bloemhoff in Milan next week. It includes the product line Everything but the Desktop by @daphnalaurens . "Following a successful first edition of Transitions, Baars & Bloemhoff once again invited six designers to imagine and shape its decorative materials in Transitions II. â€˜On top organisersâ€™, â€˜above lampâ€™ and a â€˜beside chairâ€™ are the products designed by the duo Daphna Laurens for Transitions II.  For Everything But the Desktop! the two designers went in search of the extreme limits of malleability. With a desire to use the material in ways it wasnâ€™t designed for, the duo glued together two layers of Forbo Desktop and thus created a two-tone and also double-sided, flexible material. The name of the material (Forbo Desktop) then guided the way in considering the objects that would ultimately take shape: as organisers, a lamp and an easy chair for work. These give insight into, and play with, the various properties (colour, texture, malleability) of the material." www.daphnalaurens.nl . OPERASI SESAR kerap dipilih oleh sebagian wanita lantaran dianggap lebih cepat dan tidak sakit dibandingkan persalinan secara normal. Akan tetapi, bekas luka operasi bisa menimbulkan nyeri jika tidak dirawat dengan baik dan benar.  Luka yang terjadi pada persalinan normal hanya terdapat pada jalan lahir yang memang sudah diciptakan. Sedangkan pada operasi caesar, jalan lahir dibuat melalui perut dan membuka rahim. Ada perbedaan dalam proses penyembuhan luka pada persalinan normal dan persalinan denganÂ operasi caesar. Wanita dengan persalinan normal biasanya diperbolehkan pulang atau hanya menginap satu hari di rumah sakit. Sedangkan wanita yang menjalani operasi caesar, biasanya diharuskan menginap selama tiga hari.  Proses penyembuhan luka operasi caesar sendiri biasanya memakan waktu sekitar 3- 6 bulan. Itupun tergantung dari ada tidaknya infeksi aliran darah ke daerah luka, nutrisi, dan penyakit yang diderita.  Tingkat nyeri luka bekas operasi caesar juga berbeda- beda. Perbedaan panjang luka, proses penjahitan luka, dan kondisi psikologis turut memengaruhi keparahan nyeri tersebut. Pada sebagian besar kasus, rasa nyeri sudah tidak dirasakan dalam kurun waktu enam minggu setelah melahirkan.  Namun ada beberapa faktor yang dapat memperlambat penyembuhan. Misalnya: adanya peregangan pada daerah sekitar luka dan tekanan pada perut akibat aktivitas berat atau pergerakan tertentu. Untuk mengatasinya, dokter memberikan obat nyeri.  Pada umumnya, obat antinyeri sudah cukup untuk mengatasi luka bekasoperasi caesar.  Akan tetapi, untuk mendapatkan obat pereda nyeri dibutuhkan rekomendasi dokter. The Egyptians had a preoccupation with the afterlife. This life was merely finite and a preparation for the afterlife- which would be an idealised version of one's current life. They were not believers in art for art's sake- their tombs were almost like resurrection machines- their walls covered in magical spells to convey the person soul (their "Ka") safely through the tribulations of the underworld into 'The land of the two fields'. The images shown on the walls of the tombs show the idealised version of a persons life (in accordance to their rank and social status) which they aspired to attain in the afterlife. Here are scenes from the tomb of Nebamun from the British Museum. Nebamun here is shown hunting wild birds from a barge on the Nile, accompanied by his wife and daughter. The artistic details of the various birds and wildlife are astounding and contradict the widely held view that Egyptian art "all looks the same". Above all this shows us that the ancient Egyptians, although having lived 3500 years ago, were no different to us- they too, despite the ceremonial paraphernalia that surrounds their civilisation and their preoccupation with their mortality, wanted to live and enjoy life, although forever. . . . . . . . . . . . . . . #britishmuseum #egyptian #museum #egypt #spring #nature #flowers #sky #clouds #beauty #fitfam #fitness #fit #igers #gainz #wanderer #canon #summer #landscapes #landscape #instavsco #instatravel #travel  #traveller #wanderlust #london #londoner #architecture #landscapephotography #landscape_captures

Tomb of Shah Rukn-e-Alam is the finest building in Multan, built almost 800 years ago, with red brick, bounded with beams of shisham wood. At the time of its construction it was the largest building of Mausoleum until â€˜Gol Gumbadâ€™ i.e. the mausoleum of Sultan Adil Shah was built in Bijapur, India in 17th century Ad. Reportedly it was got built by a Tughlaq King of India, Sultan Ghiasuddin Tughlaq during the years 1320-1324 AD for himself. He died in 1325 in an accident in Delhi where he had built a new city called Tughlaqabad where another tomb was got built by him where he was buried. So the whole story is confusing. It appears that the king got the building of mausoleum started in Multan for himself. Later he revised his plans and got another mausoleum built in Tughlaqabad area of Delhi. On his sudden death in 1325, he was succeeded by his son Mohammad bin Tughlaq who later got this tomb at Multan completed and presented it for burial of his patron saint Shah Rukn-e-Alam when the later died in 1335 AD at the age of 84 years. (It is interesting to note that Mohammad bin Tughlaq was born in Kotla Tolay Khan, an ancient mohallah of Multan. Perhaps he might have thought for his own burial in Multan. He died in Thatha in 1351 and was buried in Delhi). Anyhow, the building of the tomb is the most imposing and largest in Pakistan. It is octagonal. The total height of the building from ground level is 100 feet. Hundreds of people come to pay homage to the saint daily from far and wide of Pakistan.  #ZK #ZohaibKhan #blessings #of #God #blessed #Look #Lookbook #singer #artist #model #blogger #followme #jb #justinbieber #zaynmalik #zayn #kyliejenner #kendalljenner #kimkardashian #ladygaga #eminem #london #paris #newyork #hollywood #fashion #style #love â˜»

1. Asparagus membuat warna urin hijau  Asparagus merupakan makanan yang biasanya diolah menjadi sup lezat. Asparagus mengandung asam asparagusic. Senyawa ini adalah senyawa yang akan terpecah menjadi kelompok senyawa sulfur saat Anda memakannya.  Sulfur adalah senyawa yang terdapat di dalam gas dan akan disemprotkan oleh sigung ketika sedang dalam keadaan terancam. Senyawa-senyawa ini yang ketika masuk ke dalam urin akan menyebabkan warna kencing menjadi kuning gelap atau kehijauan.  2. Ikan salmon membuat urin berwarna kuning  Ikan salmon yang mengandung vitamin B-6 dapat membantu tubuh dalam menyintesis protein dan lemak. Vitamin B-6 merupakan vitamin yang sangat penting bagi tubuh. Namun, vitamin ini memiliki beberapa efek untuk saluran kemih.  Terlalu banyak mengonsumsi makanan yang mengandung vitamin B-6 akan menyebabkan urin Anda menjadi berwarna kuning. Urin Anda juga akan memiliki bau yang mirip dengan obat.  3. Buah naga membuat air kencingÂ berwarna pink  Jika Anda baru saja makanÂ buah naga merah, maka jangan khawatir, jika urin Anda menjadi merah atau sedikit berwarna pink, karena warna urin atau feses yang berubah warna menjadi kemerahan adalah memang karena efek buah naga.  Buah naga mengandung pigmen betahiasin yang kerap kali digunakan sebagai pewarna makanan alami. Ketika seseorang mengonsumsi buah ini, maka urin akan berwarna kemerahan atau disebut dengan pseudohematuria (pipis merah palsu). . 4. Wortel membuat air kencing menjadi oranye  Untuk Anda yang memiliki pola hidup sehat, dan punya hobi meminum sayuran dengan cara dijus, jangan heran jika Anda memiliki urin yang berwarna kuning gelap atau berwarna oren. Terutama jika Anda telah meminum jus wortel atau terlalu banyak mengonsumsi wortel. Join us for the preview of Luke Diiorioâ€™s second solo exhibition with the gallery on 27 April 2017. The exhibition comprises a new series of paintings which further explore the formal properties of folding and how the fold itself has become a new type of surface. â€¢ Like Kenneth Nolandâ€™s use of horizontal stripes and concentric rings, Diiorio asserts the presence of colour in this body of work. However, whilst Noland sought to integrate colour as closely as possible with the canvas in order to emphasise its flatness, Diiorio instead seeks to break up the picture plane. Bands of colour are both visually and physically separated; a distinct boundary is delineated by the artist, isolating the surface of the canvas and all that happens within its confines. Diiorio shifts emphasis from the performative act of folding, as manifested by his earlier work, to instead focus on the actual surface that is generated. For instance, subtle and diffused variations in tone, achieved by mixing beeswax into the pigment, become heightened due to this focus. Despite this isolation, the viewer is compelled to read each component in relation to one another. Where paintings were once composed of folds of varying size and thickness, the artist has modulated the bands of fabric in this new series, emphasising minimal differences which arise between them. Here, the fold becomes a unique vehicle for content. â€¢ #lukediioro #upcoming #pippyhouldsworthgallery #exhibition #painting #london #fold

Perfect match ğŸŒŸğŸŒŸğŸŒŸ Everyone dreaming about perfect skin, and good foundation, - is something that can make this dream come true. Here are some of my favourites: 1. Dior Nude Air - the lightest coverage from all with velvet matte finish on the skin. Good for normal skin without visible imperfections. 2. Temptu AirPod foundation - I couldn't resist the latest Temptu product - Air makeup is hottest trend for celebrities on red carpet. The smallest molecules of foundation, applied with AirPod machine makes skin look fresh, luminous and most important natural! To cover spots and other small imperfections foundation can be applied over the top and won't create a "cake" finish. Very useful for outdoor shooting when you need to correct model makeup on the go.  3. Laura Mercier Candleglow - light to medium coverage formula with luminous glowing finish. Good for normal/dry skin. If you want to create healthy glowing look, and use creamy texture for the rest of the makeup - Candleglow will be perfect choice. 4. Bobbi brown - not just foundation. In combination with serum ingredients it's not only covering, but also working as a treatment on a deeper layers for normal to dry skin. I think it's very good concept, but on my normal skin I felt it a little heavy, probably someone who need more moisture it will be the perfect match. But overall it gives flawless yet natural look and have good SPF factor. 5. Tom Ford - medium to full coverage that is easy to build up or sheer down. I wouldn't use it on the dry skin - it will appear a little "patchy", normal to combination will work the best with this foundation. If you like slightly heavier coverage during the day without feeling heavy on the skin - Tom Ford it's good choice.  P.S. it's not only important what you apply, but also how you apply your foundation. Different types of brushes playing important role on how foundation will appear on your skin. I am not big fan of "flat" brushes - they will work better to build-up the coverage and I love natural light finish - so my favourites are "fluffy" brushes (Shik brush 10T, Innisfree) and for "polished" look I use double side brush from @shikbrush 9TK.

Things to keep in mind while designing a community center -  The local and cultural activities contribute significantly in exactly satisfying the local needs.  As we know the needs and demands for each community are different, it is very important to conduct a study on community centre design that looks deeply into local issues.  Concisely, community centre design should not only use the same building typology for all locations but a suitable architecture typology for that particular community only. ... and we are at glue up stage 1.  Note that I am okay with the glue drips. Why? Because some squeeze out tells me that I have applied enough glue for the joint to hold for decades.  I've also prepared, meticulously. Dry clamped the piece so I can see how the joints mate and made minute adjustments as needed. Taped off the bottom support so that any glue that goes into it will easily pop off.  Finally, while the piece was dry clamped together, I waxed the interior corners. That way when the glue hardens I can take a sharp chisel and it will pop right off without any damage to the finish.
